pageContext.description: Plain rod of circular section, bent into bracelet form, it narrows towards the ends, which appear to have been cut and damaged in recent times.
pageContext.associations: Entered in the Museum Register under the year 1875 as "stated to have been found by Stephen Molloy, Police pernsioner, about a year and a half ago, in his land ajoining a lake, together with a thin gold plate."
pageContext.collection: National Museum of Science and Art, Dublin,PLate XVIII. 382. 105. 1875
pageContext.museumCollection: National Museum of Science & Art, Dublin
